<item>
            <title>[LU-12931] Fix minor errors with cfs_time_seconds usage</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12931</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;cfs_time_seconds() converts seconds to jiffies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately the name might suggest it returns seconds, rather than consumes them, so it is worth while doing an occasion audit to make sure it isn&apos;t being misused.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At time of writing there is one place (in delayed_msg_check) where it is used but not needed (we have seconds and want seconds), and two places (ptl_recover_import and mgc_process_log) where the returned value is stored in a variable called &quot;sec&quot;.&#160; The variable is used correctly as jiffies, but the name is confusing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These irregularities should be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
